items.title: Minuria integerrima
items.content_text: A single flowering plant.

items.title: Senecio platylepis
items.content_text: Annual herb less than 40cm tall. Only this single flowering plant observed. Previous weeks have seen very good rains.

items.title: Xanthium strumarium spp. agg.
items.content_text: Growing along edge of Murray River.

items.title: Goodenia fascicularis
items.content_text: Not especially silky, but all other characters point to Goodenia fascicularis, which has previously been observed in this area.

items.title: Sarcozona praecox
items.content_text: Differentiate from co-existing Noon-flower by triangular cross-section of leaves, paler leaves that are often red-tinged, and flowers that do not ascend above leaves (in Noon-flower flowers sit above leaves).

items.title: Osteocarpum salsuginosum
items.content_text:
Growing near edge of Alectryon oleifolius tree. Not commonly encountered here.
Fruit required to confidently differentiate from very similar Osteocarpum acropterum.

items.title: Silene apetala var. apetala
items.content_text: Exotic annual herb, growing here less than 20cm tall near the base of Alectryon oleifolius subsp. canescens.

items.title: Rhodanthe stricta
items.content_text: Single plant observed at this location, within 25 metres of Murray River bank. Rare plant across this landscape.

items.title: Fumaria bastardii
items.content_text: Only a single, small patch of plants observed growing within 20 metres of Murray River bank.

items.title: Bulbine semibarbata
items.content_text: Note the hair tufts at the base of stamens on the longer three filaments only. Bulbine alata has hair tufts at the base of each stamen.

items.title: Pogona vitticeps, Sonchus asper subsp. asper
items.content_text: Central Bearded Dragon feeding on the flowers of Sonchus asper (Sow Thistle).

items.title: Nicotiana glauca
items.content_text: Standing beside plants: Peter Barnes (right), Russell Best (front left), James Booth (left hidden).

items.title: Eremophila divaricata subsp. divaricata
items.content_text: White-flowering form.
